Preheat your oven to 200°C and put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil for the pasta. Remove the root and dark green top from the @leek{1/2}, halve lengthways and thinly slice into half moons.

Chop the @broccoli{1/2} into small florets (little trees) and then chop your @chives{1/2} as small as you can (or use #scissors{} if it's easier).

Once the water is boiling, add the @penne pasta{100%g} to the pan. When it has been cooking for ~{3%minutes}, add the broccoli and cook for another ~{4%minutes}. When both the pasta and broccoli are cooked, drain into a #colander{} and pop them back into the pan. Mix in half the @unsalted butter{15%g} and season with a good pinch of salt and a generous grind of @pepper{}. Keep to one side.

While your pasta cooks, heat another large saucepan over medium heat and add the remaining @unsalted butter{15%g}. When the butter has melted, add the chopped leek and cook for ~{4-5%minutes} or until softened. Stir occasionally. Season generously with pepper and then stir in the @crème fraîche{100%g}. Add the @fish stock powder{1/2} and stir to dissolve. Add the @smoked fish mix{215%g} and stir gently to make sure all the fish is coated in the sauce.

Transfer the creamy fish mix to an #ovenproof dish{}. Spread the pasta and broccoli on top, sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} and bake for ~{15%minutes}.

> TIP: If it looks like the pasta is becoming too brown, simply cover it with foil for the last 5 mins.

When the seafood pasta bake is golden on top remove it from your oven and leave it to sit for a minute or two. Sprinkle on the chopped chives and spoon into #bowls{}. Enjoy!